winterVersion = "I write to you now without flourish, for I have no patience for insipid flattery or hollow words. The weight of the crown that will soon rest upon your head is heavy. I know this. I have worn armor, shed blood, and borne scars all for the sake of my people. Your kingdom faces devastation; in this, words cannot adequately express my condolences for the challenges you face. And yet, I see in you a burning resolve to carry forward your father’s legacy when the time soon comes—and to shape your own, no doubt. 

