springVersion = "I am sincerely flattered that, in the face of such incredibly trying times, you afford some of your spirit into acknowledging my initial outreach. As our situations grow ever more dire, the only logical choice is for us to join forces and pool our kingdoms’ resources. Our military can stifle any looming civilian uprising, while your support will be invaluable in quelling any internal dissent on the mountain. 

You are aware, I am sure, of recent incidents involving unsanctioned magic usage among the clans. The Council grows less confident with each day that we will be able to stifle these mana-mad dissidents. They seek shortcuts, unaware there are none to be found in matters of war and steel. 

That being said, I know you are concerned about assassins. Please rest assured that none will be found in Durvash. To kill another in deceit is the highest dishonor, and vanquishes one’s hopes of reaching the Silver Halls. There is not a dwarf alive who would risk it—this holds true even for the magic-sick “innovators”. They may be naive, but even they retain some respect for the laws of our gods. Therefore, let this letter be a warning and a reassurance. 

May your blades remain sharp as you consider my words. The time is fast approaching when you will need them."
